==English==
===Etymology===
Used in [[w:English language|English]] around the 15th century. [[compound noun|Compound]] of [[lime]] and [[twig]], with [[lime]] referring to [[birdlime]].
===Noun===
'''lime-twig''' or '''[[lime twig]]'''
# A twig used for [[catch]]ing [[bird]]s that is [[smear]]ed with birdlime.